---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const seo = {"title": "Threads — Smooth Threads | D‑Essence Wellness", "description": "Collagen‑stimulating threads for subtle refinement and firmness.", "canonical": "/services/smooth-threads", "type": "website", "ogImage": "/og-default" };
---

<BaseLayout {...seo}>

<section class="relative isolate paper">

<style is:global>
  :root{
    --paper:#F8F6F2; --ink:#141414; --muted:#5a5a5a; --rule:#E6E1D8;
  }
  .paper{ background:var(--paper); color:var(--ink); }
  .rule{ border-color:var(--rule); }
  .muted{ color:var(--muted); }
  .measure{ max-width: 64ch; }
  .dropcap:first-letter{ float:left; font-size:3.2rem; line-height:1; padding-right:.35rem; padding-top:.2rem; font-weight:600; }
  .ataglance{ display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:.75rem 1.25rem; font-size:.95rem; color:var(--muted); }
  .ataglance span::after{ content:"·"; margin-left:1.25rem; color:var(--muted); }
  .ataglance span:last-child::after{ content:""; margin:0; }
  .pullquote{ border-left:2px solid var(--ink); padding-left:.85rem; font-style:italic; color:#3b3b3b; margin: 1.25rem 0; }
  @media (max-width: 1023px){ .side-col{ display:none; } }
  details.faq summary{ list-style:none; }
  details.faq summary::-webkit-details-marker{ display:none; }
  .faq-toggle{ width:1.1rem; height:1.1rem; margin-right:.5rem; flex:0 0 auto; }
  details.faq[open] .plus{ display:none; }
  details.faq:not([open]) .minus{ display:none; }
  .icon-check{ width:1.1rem; height:1.1rem; flex:0 0 auto; margin-top:.15rem;}
  .timeline{ position:relative; }
  .timeline::before{ content:""; position:absolute; left:.9rem; top:.25rem; bottom:.25rem; width:2px; background:var(--rule); }
  .tl-step{ position:relative; padding-left:2.25rem; }
  .tl-badge{ position:absolute; left:0; top:.1rem; width:1.8rem; height:1.8rem; border-radius:999px; background:var(--ink); color:#fff; font-size:.9rem; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; font-weight:600; }
  .tl-title{ font-weight:600; }
</style>

  <!-- HERO (left‑aligned, no breadcrumb) -->
  <div class="px-6 pt-28 md:pt-32 pb-10">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
      <div class="service-head">
  <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
    <div class="service-hero">
  <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-end md:justify-between gap-8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-400 to-cyan-400"></span>
        <div class="service-hero v4 border-l-4 border-neutral-200 dark:border-white/10 pl-5 md:pl-6">
  <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full border px-2.5 py-1 text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.20em] text-neutral-600/80">Service</span>
  <h1 class="mt-3 text-5xl md:text-7xl font-semibold leading-tight tracking-tight">Threads — Smooth Threads</h1>
  <p class="mt-3 text-lg md:text-xl muted measure leading-relaxed">Collagen‑stimulating threads for subtle refinement and firmness.</p>
  <div class="mt-6 h-px bg-neutral-200/80 dark:bg-white/10"></div>
</div>

    </div>
    <div class="md:w-80">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border rule/70 bg-white/40 dark:bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-sm p-4 md:p-5">
        <div class="h-24 w-full rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-br from-emerald-300/40 via-cyan-300/35 to-transparent"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mt-8 h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-neutral-300/70 dark:via-white/15 to-transparent"></div>
</div>

<div class="mt-6 border-t rule"></div>
  <div class="mt-6 border-t rule"></div>
</div>

      <div class="mt-6 h-px w-full border-t rule"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- BODY -->
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 pb-24 grid grid-cols-12 gap-8">

    <!-- Removed left side labels entirely -->

    <!-- Main narrative -->
    <article class="col-span-12 lg:col-span-8 xl:col-span-7">
      <!-- DESCRIPTION (unique, professional) -->
      <section id="description" class="measure">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Description</h2>
<p class="mt-3 muted dropcap">PDO Smooth Threads are fine, absorbable polydioxanone sutures placed just beneath the skin to stimulate your own collagen and improve skin quality over time. Unlike barbed “lifting” threads, smooth threads do not reposition tissue—instead they create a supportive collagen matrix that softens fine lines, refines texture, and enhances firmness in a subtle, natural way.</p>
<p class="mt-3 muted">Treatments are typically performed as a series every 4–6 weeks, with collagen remodeling continuing for months. As the PDO material dissolves, new collagen helps maintain results—many clients notice progressive improvement over 3–6 months, with benefits that can last up to 12 months. There are no incisions and downtime is minimal.</p>
<div class="mt-4 ataglance">
  <span>Series every 4–6 weeks</span><span>No incisions</span><span>Collagen‑stimulating</span><span>Benefits up to 12 months</span>
</div>
<p class="pullquote">“Subtle smoothing via collagen stimulation—not a lift.”</p>
      </section>

      <div class="my-10 h-px border-t rule"></div>

      <!-- BENEFITS (unchanged from v2) -->
      <section id="benefits" class="measure">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Benefits</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-10 gap-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3 muted"><svg class="icon-check" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M20 7L10 17l-6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg>Smooths frown lines, forehead creases, and crow’s feet.</div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3 muted"><svg class="icon-check" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M20 7L10 17l-6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg>Preserves natural expression, avoids “frozen” look.</div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3 muted"><svg class="icon-check" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M20 7L10 17l-6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg>Quick procedure with minimal downtime.</div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3 muted"><svg class="icon-check" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M20 7L10 17l-6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg>Pure formulation reduces risk of antibody resistance.</div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="my-10 h-px border-t rule"></div>

      <!-- THE PROCESS (unchanged from v2) -->
      <section id="process" class="measure">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">The Process</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 timeline space-y-6">
          <div class="tl-step"><div class="tl-badge">1</div><p class="tl-title">Consultation</p><p class="muted mt-1">Assessment of goals and medical history, mapping injection points and confirming candidacy.</p></div>
          <div class="tl-step"><div class="tl-badge">2</div><p class="tl-title">Treatment</p><p class="muted mt-1">Small injections with a fine needle into targeted muscles; procedure usually takes 10–15 minutes.</p></div>
          <div class="tl-step"><div class="tl-badge">3</div><p class="tl-title">Follow‑Up</p><p class="muted mt-1">Results develop in 3–5 days with full effect at 2 weeks. Effects last about 3–4 months.</p></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="my-10 h-px border-t rule"></div>

      <!-- PRE / POST (unchanged from v2) -->
      <section id="care" class="measure">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Pre and Post‑Treatment Instructions</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-10">
          <div><p class="font-medium">Before your visit</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 muted mt-2 space-y-2"><li>Avoid blood‑thinning meds/supplements (aspirin, NSAIDs, fish oil, vitamin E) ~7 days unless prescribed—consult your provider.</li><li>No alcohol for 24 hours before treatment.</li><li>Reschedule if you have an active skin infection or cold sore in the area.</li><li>Share allergies, pregnancy/breastfeeding status, and recent procedures with your provider.</li></ul>
          </div>
          <div><p class="font-medium">After your visit</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 muted mt-2 space-y-2"><li>Avoid strenuous exercise, excessive facial movements, and pressure on treated areas for 24–48 hours.</li><li>Use cool packs intermittently; expect mild swelling/bruise that resolves within ~1 week.</li><li>Avoid heat/sauna and direct sun for 24–48 hours; wear SPF.</li><li>No facials/laser on the area for 1–2 weeks unless cleared by your provider.</li></ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="my-10 h-px border-t rule"></div>

      <!-- FAQs (unchanged from v2) -->
      <section id="faqs" class="measure">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3">
          <details class="faq"><summary class="flex items-center cursor-pointer">What are Smooth PDO Threads and how do they work?</summary><p class="muted mt-2 ml-6">They are fine, dissolvable sutures placed under the skin to stimulate collagen and elastin. As the threads dissolve, a new collagen scaffold remains, improving firmness and texture.</p></details>
          <details class="faq"><summary class="flex items-center cursor-pointer">Do smooth threads lift like barbed threads?</summary><p class="muted mt-2 ml-6">No. Smooth threads do not physically pull tissue; they focus on collagen induction. For lift, barbed threads may be combined when appropriate.</p></details>
          <details class="faq"><summary class="flex items-center cursor-pointer">When will I see results and how long do they last?</summary><p class="muted mt-2 ml-6">Results build gradually over 4–12 weeks as collagen forms. After a series, benefits commonly persist ~12–18 months, with maintenance as needed.</p></details>
          <details class="faq"><summary class="flex items-center cursor-pointer">Is the treatment painful and what’s the downtime?</summary><p class="muted mt-2 ml-6">Discomfort is usually minimal with topical/local numbing. Expect mild redness or swelling that resolves quickly; most resume routine activities the same day.</p></details>
          <details class="faq"><summary class="flex items-center cursor-pointer">What areas can be treated?</summary><p class="muted mt-2 ml-6">Common targets include forehead lines, crow’s feet, smoker’s lines, nasolabial folds, marionette lines, cheeks, jawline/chin, and neck; select acne scars may also improve.</p></details>
        </div>
      </section>
    </article>

    <!-- Right margin notes (sticky cues) remain -->
    
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>
